1
00:00:24,930 --> 00:00:26,810
♪Wine banners flutter, carriages pass by♪

2
00:00:26,810 --> 00:00:29,610
♪The streets ablaze with revelry♪

3
00:00:32,440 --> 00:00:34,240
♪His name in gold, proud blooms adorn♪

4
00:00:34,240 --> 00:00:37,260
♪Who lingers now♪

5
00:00:39,080 --> 00:00:40,320
♪Seek one true peace♪

6
00:00:40,320 --> 00:00:42,250
♪Yet fate hangs on a thread so fine♪

7
00:00:42,680 --> 00:00:43,970
♪Longing has taken root♪

8
00:00:43,970 --> 00:00:46,140
♪Like flowers yet not♪

9
00:00:46,700 --> 00:00:48,120
♪Words fall too short♪

10
00:00:48,120 --> 00:00:50,040
♪So I ride far♪

11
00:00:50,040 --> 00:00:52,780
♪To chase the dream beyond the skyline♪

12
00:00:53,040 --> 00:00:54,200
♪No regret♪

13
00:00:54,200 --> 00:00:55,790
♪Through the flow of years♪

14
00:00:55,790 --> 00:00:57,580
♪Over waves and cliffs♪

15
00:00:57,580 --> 00:00:58,830
♪Where worries end♪

16
00:00:58,830 --> 00:01:01,360
♪May winds bear word of who recalls♪

17
00:01:01,360 --> 00:01:02,940
♪But fate cries loud♪

18
00:01:02,940 --> 00:01:04,920
♪Envying a world too pure to keep♪

19
00:01:04,920 --> 00:01:07,580
♪Seasons bloom, yet lips grow weak♪

20
00:01:07,930 --> 00:01:09,850
♪Through dust of time, all mortals stray♪

21
00:01:09,850 --> 00:01:11,600
♪As seasons weave their gold and grey♪

22
00:01:11,600 --> 00:01:13,560
♪I roam the earth and heavens freely♪

23
00:01:13,560 --> 00:01:15,390
♪Why ask the road back home to be♪

24
00:01:15,600 --> 00:01:18,010
♪Sun and moon part, stars remain silent♪

25
00:01:18,010 --> 00:01:22,510
♪Through endless night, dawn paints its art♪

26
00:01:24,460 --> 00:01:29,980
=Serendipity=

27
00:01:30,020 --> 00:01:32,940
=Episode 10=

28
00:01:51,310 --> 00:01:52,640
Buddy.

29
00:01:57,120 --> 00:01:58,480
Is that you?

30
00:02:08,590 --> 00:02:09,630
Buddy!

31
00:02:11,800 --> 00:02:13,030
Is that you?

32
00:02:43,240 --> 00:02:44,470
(What's going on?)

33
00:02:45,190 --> 00:02:46,560
(Am I losing my mind?)

34
00:03:11,800 --> 00:03:13,310
Aren't you ready yet?

35
00:03:15,910 --> 00:03:17,080
Patience, my lord.

36
00:03:18,280 --> 00:03:19,520
I'm ready now.

37
00:04:15,310 --> 00:04:18,630
You seem to be in a good mood today.

38
00:04:44,600 --> 00:04:46,750
The Shuisheng Powder is tasteless,

39
00:04:47,270 --> 00:04:49,870
inducing truth-telling in twilight sleep,

40
00:04:50,310 --> 00:04:51,630
yet memories fade upon waking.

41
00:05:01,120 --> 00:05:02,680
Where is my brother now?

42
00:05:06,680 --> 00:05:08,720
You've been cooped up here for days.

43
00:05:08,920 --> 00:05:11,270
I brought you food from Longfeng Restaurant.

44
00:05:11,270 --> 00:05:13,600
(Yaji Hall)
Ring cake, osmanthus cake,

45
00:05:13,800 --> 00:05:15,680
and chestnut crisp,

46
00:05:15,680 --> 00:05:16,920
all my favorites.

47
00:05:17,720 --> 00:05:19,270
Mr. Song, you're so kind.

48
00:05:24,190 --> 00:05:25,030
Slow down.

49
00:05:26,920 --> 00:05:28,190
If you keep coming in like this

50
00:05:28,310 --> 00:05:29,390
and get seen by others,

51
00:05:29,600 --> 00:05:30,800
aren't you afraid

52
00:05:30,800 --> 00:05:32,630
that it will damage your noble reputation?

53
00:05:33,190 --> 00:05:34,390
Even if word gets out,

54
00:05:34,480 --> 00:05:35,720
as told in love tales,

55
00:05:35,920 --> 00:05:37,630
I'm risking everything for love.

56
00:05:38,270 --> 00:05:39,120
In my opinion,

57
00:05:39,120 --> 00:05:40,510
it's an honor, not a shame.

58
00:05:40,510 --> 00:05:41,630
It's something I've been longing for.

59
00:05:41,800 --> 00:05:43,720
You truly are a man

60
00:05:44,040 --> 00:05:46,040
of loyalty and responsibility.

61
00:05:46,720 --> 00:05:47,720
Lady Mingshu,

62
00:05:49,070 --> 00:05:50,600
not everything I said that day

63
00:05:51,120 --> 00:05:52,270
was an act.

64
00:05:55,430 --> 00:05:56,630
If I love someone,

65
00:05:57,480 --> 00:06:00,120
I'll marry her regardless of her status

66
00:06:00,680 --> 00:06:01,920
or background.

67
00:06:04,600 --> 00:06:05,680
I'll cherish her, protect her,

68
00:06:06,680 --> 00:06:08,510
and never waver under others' judgment.

69
00:06:11,700 --> 00:06:14,460
(Yaji Hall)

70
00:06:17,160 --> 00:06:20,630
I wonder which young lady

71
00:06:21,000 --> 00:06:22,070
will be so lucky to have you.

72
00:06:22,070 --> 00:06:23,640
- Actually, that young lady...
- You are here.

73
00:06:25,310 --> 00:06:26,160
Hello, Mr. Song.

74
00:06:27,680 --> 00:06:29,390
Mr. Song brought snacks!

75
00:06:29,390 --> 00:06:30,230
Come on.

76
00:06:30,720 --> 00:06:31,560
Sit down.

77
00:06:34,950 --> 00:06:35,790
Try this.

78
00:06:37,120 --> 00:06:38,390
Thank you, Mr. Song.

79
00:06:38,870 --> 00:06:40,510
But this place is too public.

80
00:06:40,920 --> 00:06:42,600
You should visit less frequently.

81
00:06:45,720 --> 00:06:48,310
It's no big deal just to bring some food.

82
00:06:49,830 --> 00:06:51,600
We're here under borrowed identities.

83
00:06:52,510 --> 00:06:53,750
Your noble status

84
00:06:54,310 --> 00:06:55,600
draws attention.

85
00:06:56,680 --> 00:06:57,560
Don't you agree?

86
00:06:58,270 --> 00:06:59,510
You're right.

87
00:07:00,000 --> 00:07:01,040
I wasn't considerate.

88
00:07:04,600 --> 00:07:05,440
I've made up my mind.

89
00:07:06,360 --> 00:07:07,870
I'll join your plan.

90
00:07:13,270 --> 00:07:14,750
Lu Wencai did deceive me.

91
00:07:15,120 --> 00:07:17,240
He got the jade pendant from somewhere

92
00:07:17,430 --> 00:07:18,630
and set a trap for me.

93
00:07:19,070 --> 00:07:20,240
I was such a fool

94
00:07:20,510 --> 00:07:21,600
to believe him.

95
00:07:22,680 --> 00:07:23,600
Have you found any leads

96
00:07:23,600 --> 00:07:24,510
about your brother?

97
00:07:25,070 --> 00:07:26,160
He couldn't make it clear either,

98
00:07:26,390 --> 00:07:28,240
and then he couldn't say anything more.

99
00:07:30,680 --> 00:07:31,520
Since you've agreed

100
00:07:31,800 --> 00:07:33,390
to testify against Lu Wencai at the Banquet,

101
00:07:34,120 --> 00:07:35,070
we'll stop

102
00:07:35,600 --> 00:07:36,680
hiding the truth from you.

103
00:07:44,430 --> 00:07:47,120
So the story of childhood sweethearts

104
00:07:48,430 --> 00:07:49,830
and drifting performers

105
00:07:51,270 --> 00:07:52,190
are all lies?

106
00:07:53,630 --> 00:07:54,470
Yes.

107
00:07:55,310 --> 00:07:58,190
We assumed false identities to come here

108
00:07:58,720 --> 00:08:00,720
to gather information on your father.

109
00:08:01,720 --> 00:08:02,720
Based on my speculation,

110
00:08:03,070 --> 00:08:05,920
his false accusation of Mr. Su's embezzlement

111
00:08:06,240 --> 00:08:07,720
was very likely coerced.

112
00:08:09,680 --> 00:08:10,630
What do you plan to do?

113
00:08:11,800 --> 00:08:13,190
Mr. Su's conviction was directly tied

114
00:08:13,190 --> 00:08:15,390
to your father's testimony.

115
00:08:16,070 --> 00:08:17,920
If your father was coerced

116
00:08:17,920 --> 00:08:19,040
into exile and death,

117
00:08:19,430 --> 00:08:20,870
don't you want to know the truth?

118
00:08:21,070 --> 00:08:22,070
Of course I do.

119
00:08:23,120 --> 00:08:24,680
But scraping by is hard enough.

120
00:08:25,600 --> 00:08:26,950
How can I find out the truth?

121
00:08:28,040 --> 00:08:29,240
Don't worry.

122
00:08:29,800 --> 00:08:31,000
I'll definitely find it out.

123
00:08:31,870 --> 00:08:32,870
If we can prove

124
00:08:32,870 --> 00:08:34,150
that your father was forced,

125
00:08:34,670 --> 00:08:37,030
your sentences may be reduced.

126
00:08:37,030 --> 00:08:38,130
You may get rid of the slave status.

127
00:08:39,030 --> 00:08:39,870
Then,

128
00:08:40,000 --> 00:08:41,480
you could leave the Imperial Music Office,

129
00:08:41,910 --> 00:08:43,720
and your brother needn't hide anymore.

130
00:08:46,720 --> 00:08:48,320
I believe that you're all good people.

131
00:08:48,720 --> 00:08:49,790
Since you're trying to help me,

132
00:08:49,910 --> 00:08:51,320
I should give you something in return

133
00:08:51,670 --> 00:08:52,870
and tell you everything I know.

134
00:08:53,670 --> 00:08:55,030
Thank you, Lady Yuanying.

135
00:08:57,480 --> 00:09:00,200
My brother and I lived in our hometown

136
00:09:00,720 --> 00:09:02,030
until a year ago

137
00:09:02,120 --> 00:09:03,910
when we were suddenly abducted.

138
00:09:03,910 --> 00:09:05,440
I don't know who they were,

139
00:09:06,120 --> 00:09:07,390
but I overheard them

140
00:09:07,600 --> 00:09:09,200
threatening my father with our lives

141
00:09:09,510 --> 00:09:11,240
to do something.

142
00:09:11,720 --> 00:09:12,840
I'm not sure

143
00:09:13,030 --> 00:09:14,150
what it was.

144
00:09:14,670 --> 00:09:15,910
Did your father comply?

145
00:09:18,600 --> 00:09:19,600
Now I realize

146
00:09:20,270 --> 00:09:22,320
it must've been about framing Mr. Su.

147
00:09:23,240 --> 00:09:25,390
The kidnappers released us,

148
00:09:25,600 --> 00:09:27,270
but before we could escape far,

149
00:09:27,270 --> 00:09:28,870
the government officers showed up.

150
00:09:29,240 --> 00:09:31,080
I drew them off so my brother could flee.

151
00:09:31,510 --> 00:09:32,960
But I was caught

152
00:09:34,390 --> 00:09:36,750
and condemned to be a government slave.

153
00:09:38,320 --> 00:09:39,840
Then I learned my father had been convicted

154
00:09:41,720 --> 00:09:43,150
and my brother vanished without a trace.

155
00:09:43,870 --> 00:09:44,750
Rest assured,

156
00:09:45,510 --> 00:09:47,440
my brother will investigate this thoroughly.

157
00:09:48,600 --> 00:09:50,390
There is still a long way to go.

158
00:09:50,910 --> 00:09:52,630
We must plan for the long term.

159
00:09:55,600 --> 00:09:59,510
First, break away from Lu Wencai's control.

160
00:10:02,120 --> 00:10:03,510
What do you need me to do?

161
00:10:07,000 --> 00:10:08,480
Come on. Please.

162
00:10:11,630 --> 00:10:12,600
- Mr. Song.
- Mr. Song.

163
00:10:12,600 --> 00:10:13,440
Mr. Song.

164
00:10:14,030 --> 00:10:14,870
This way, please.

165
00:10:17,390 --> 00:10:18,790
- Mr. Song.
- Mr. Song.

166
00:10:20,910 --> 00:10:21,750
Mr. Song.

167
00:10:24,440 --> 00:10:25,670
Dear Qingzhao,

168
00:10:25,790 --> 00:10:27,750
your presence honors my humble house.

169
00:10:28,000 --> 00:10:29,030
You flatter me, Minister Lu.

170
00:10:29,240 --> 00:10:30,120
I don't deserve such praise.

171
00:10:30,120 --> 00:10:31,720
(Mengying Pavilion)

172
00:10:31,720 --> 00:10:33,270
Only Minister Lu

173
00:10:33,270 --> 00:10:35,600
could summon the Duke's legitimate grandson.

174
00:10:37,200 --> 00:10:38,720
Come on, let's raise our cups.

175
00:10:39,910 --> 00:10:40,750
Everyone,

176
00:10:41,390 --> 00:10:43,840
since my son begins his official career,

177
00:10:44,030 --> 00:10:46,870
he is a colleague of yours now.

178
00:10:46,870 --> 00:10:49,720
(Lu Zegang)
May you guide him well.

179
00:10:50,480 --> 00:10:52,600
With pleasure, Minister Lu.

180
00:10:52,600 --> 00:10:53,440
Come on.

181
00:11:01,440 --> 00:11:02,280
- Please sit.
- Please.

182
00:11:02,280 --> 00:11:03,290
- Sit.
- Please.

183
00:11:06,320 --> 00:11:07,160
Minister Lu,

184
00:11:07,790 --> 00:11:09,200
I heard that tonight,

185
00:11:09,440 --> 00:11:10,840
Liu Yuanying, the famous dancer,

186
00:11:10,840 --> 00:11:12,480
will perform the Flying Dance.

187
00:11:13,000 --> 00:11:14,480
We are eagerly looking forward to it.

188
00:11:14,480 --> 00:11:15,840
Patience, gentlemen.

189
00:11:16,320 --> 00:11:17,160
Behold!

190
00:12:19,540 --> 00:12:22,260
(Mengying Pavilion)

191
00:12:45,000 --> 00:12:47,390
(Mengying Pavilion)
Brilliant!

192
00:12:47,930 --> 00:12:48,860
Not bad.

193
00:13:10,320 --> 00:13:11,480
There she is.

194
00:13:11,790 --> 00:13:12,630
Look.

195
00:13:14,820 --> 00:13:17,060
(Mengying Pavilion)

196
00:13:18,840 --> 00:13:21,360
Lady Yuanying lives up to her reputation.

197
00:13:27,390 --> 00:13:28,910
Her crimson sleeves

198
00:13:29,840 --> 00:13:31,120
weep tales of grievance.

199
00:13:33,080 --> 00:13:35,240
The Flying Dance is really a rare sight.

200
00:13:35,440 --> 00:13:37,270
- Wonderful.
- A true marvel of the capital!

201
00:13:37,370 --> 00:13:38,600
Seeing is believing.

202
00:13:38,600 --> 00:13:39,440
Indeed.

203
00:13:40,320 --> 00:13:41,670
She endures

204
00:13:43,150 --> 00:13:44,480
life's cruelties alone.

205
00:13:53,870 --> 00:13:55,390
What heartache

206
00:13:56,670 --> 00:13:58,150
lies beneath her smile?

207
00:13:59,030 --> 00:14:01,030
It doesn't sound right.

208
00:14:01,030 --> 00:14:03,240
It seems like complaints about grievances.

209
00:14:07,120 --> 00:14:07,960
Great!

210
00:14:07,960 --> 00:14:08,970
Come on, a toast.

211
00:14:11,000 --> 00:14:12,600
Her silk dress

212
00:14:13,720 --> 00:14:15,150
is soaked in tears.

213
00:14:44,720 --> 00:14:45,600
Goodness.

214
00:14:45,600 --> 00:14:46,750
Why is Lady Yuanying

215
00:14:46,870 --> 00:14:48,080
covered in bruises?

216
00:14:49,770 --> 00:14:50,830
There really are injuries!

217
00:14:51,320 --> 00:14:52,750
You've stayed in the mansion these days.

218
00:14:53,000 --> 00:14:54,080
How did you get hurt?

219
00:15:04,200 --> 00:15:05,040
Madam!

220
00:15:05,240 --> 00:15:06,080
What's wrong?

221
00:15:06,240 --> 00:15:07,510
There's trouble at the Banquet!

222
00:15:09,100 --> 00:15:10,860
(Mengying Pavilion)

223
00:15:10,870 --> 00:15:12,600
Since Lady Yuanying is injured,

224
00:15:12,840 --> 00:15:14,750
escort her to rest and recover.

225
00:15:15,030 --> 00:15:15,870
Steward Wang,

226
00:15:15,890 --> 00:15:17,910
fetch a physician to examine her thoroughly.

227
00:15:17,910 --> 00:15:19,030
Yes, Master.

228
00:15:19,270 --> 00:15:20,120
Minister Lu,

229
00:15:20,320 --> 00:15:21,160
it's inappropriate.

230
00:15:21,160 --> 00:15:22,480
(Mengying Pavilion)

231
00:15:22,480 --> 00:15:24,320
Liu Yuanying is a government slave.

232
00:15:24,790 --> 00:15:25,700
Any incident involving her

233
00:15:26,080 --> 00:15:27,550
requires investigation and documentation.

234
00:15:28,120 --> 00:15:29,600
Since this occurred at the Lu Residence,

235
00:15:29,910 --> 00:15:31,240
failure to clarify it

236
00:15:31,600 --> 00:15:33,550
would imply negligence on your part.

237
00:15:36,120 --> 00:15:37,120
Lady Yuanying,

238
00:15:37,720 --> 00:15:39,120
if you fail to make it clear

239
00:15:39,390 --> 00:15:40,700
and stain the reputation of the Lu Family,

240
00:15:40,960 --> 00:15:42,080
can you bear the consequences?

241
00:15:42,910 --> 00:15:43,750
Lady Yuanying,

242
00:15:44,320 --> 00:15:45,360
every dignitary here

243
00:15:45,480 --> 00:15:47,510
serves as a pillar of the state.

244
00:15:47,790 --> 00:15:49,600
Who of them can't uphold justice for you?

245
00:15:50,720 --> 00:15:52,120
The Investigating Censor is here too.

246
00:15:52,630 --> 00:15:53,550
Mr. Chen,

247
00:15:54,080 --> 00:15:55,630
what does the law dictate?

248
00:15:56,600 --> 00:15:58,910
If a slave is harmed during service,

249
00:15:59,550 --> 00:16:01,510
the authorities must pursue accountability.

250
00:16:04,320 --> 00:16:05,320
Is it related to you?

251
00:16:05,600 --> 00:16:06,750
Absolutely not.

252
00:16:10,000 --> 00:16:11,320
Well, in that case,

253
00:16:11,480 --> 00:16:13,910
Lady Yuanying, you should speak plainly.

254
00:16:14,120 --> 00:16:15,200
We'll definitely

255
00:16:15,200 --> 00:16:16,960
give you an explanation.

256
00:16:31,000 --> 00:16:32,440
It's the young master of Lu.

257
00:16:38,220 --> 00:16:39,240
Unbelievable!

258
00:16:39,240 --> 00:16:40,340
Indeed. Unbelievable.

259
00:16:41,320 --> 00:16:43,270
During our stay at the mansion for rehearsal,

260
00:16:43,720 --> 00:16:45,390
he sneaked into my room, raped me,

261
00:16:45,910 --> 00:16:46,960
and abused me.

262
00:16:46,960 --> 00:16:48,720
(Mengying Pavilion)

263
00:16:48,720 --> 00:16:50,510
I never touched you!

264
00:16:50,510 --> 00:16:51,960
How could I rape you?

265
00:16:52,510 --> 00:16:55,120
Father, this is slander!

266
00:16:57,120 --> 00:16:58,440
Stop telling lies!

267
00:16:58,790 --> 00:17:00,360
With so many dignitaries here,

268
00:17:00,480 --> 00:17:01,840
how dear I lie?

269
00:17:02,080 --> 00:17:03,240
It's the young master of the Lu.

270
00:17:03,720 --> 00:17:05,480
During our stay for rehearsal,

271
00:17:05,480 --> 00:17:06,320
he sneaked into my room,

272
00:17:06,320 --> 00:17:08,440
raped me, and abused me.

273
00:17:08,830 --> 00:17:10,270
You're spouting false accusations!

274
00:17:13,880 --> 00:17:16,000
You and Mr. Lu have conflicting accounts.

275
00:17:16,200 --> 00:17:17,400
Lack of proof

276
00:17:17,550 --> 00:17:19,590
will condemn you for false accusations.

277
00:17:21,830 --> 00:17:24,400
But how can I prove it?

278
00:17:31,680 --> 00:17:33,960
I know the location of Mr. Lu's birthmark.

279
00:17:34,550 --> 00:17:35,790
There is a black birthmark

280
00:17:35,880 --> 00:17:37,400
below his buttocks.

281
00:17:41,680 --> 00:17:42,520
Stop being panicking.

282
00:17:45,270 --> 00:17:46,110
She is lying!

283
00:17:46,510 --> 00:17:47,350
Everyone,

284
00:17:47,880 --> 00:17:50,350
I don't have such a birthmark.

285
00:17:50,920 --> 00:17:51,760
You're just in time.

286
00:17:52,200 --> 00:17:53,040
